{"award_age":81.0,"bio_image":null,"category":"Peace","country":"France","date_of_birth":"1887-10-05T00:00:00.000Z","date_of_death":"1976-02-20T00:00:00.000Z","gender":"male","image_urls":[],"link":"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Ren%C3%A9_Cassin","mini_bio":"<p><b>Ren\u00e9 Samuel Cassin<\/b> (5 October 1887 in <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Bayonne\" title=\"Bayonne\">Bayonne<\/a>, <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/French_Basque_Country\" title=\"French Basque Country\">Basque Country<\/a>, <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/France\" title=\"France\">France<\/a> \u2013 20 February 1976 in <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Paris\" title=\"Paris\">Paris<\/a>, France) was a <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/France\" title=\"France\">French<\/a> <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Lawyer\" title=\"Lawyer\">jurist<\/a>, <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Universit%C3%A9_Lille_Nord_de_France\" title=\"Universit\u00e9 Lille Nord de France\" class=\"mw-redirect\">law professor<\/a> and <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Judge\" title=\"Judge\">judge<\/a>. The son of a French-Jewish merchant, he served as a soldier in <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/World_War_I\" title=\"World War I\">World War I<\/a>, and later went on to form the Union F\u00e9d\u00e9rale, a leftist, pacifist Veterans organisation. He received the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Nobel_Peace_Prize\" title=\"Nobel Peace Prize\">Nobel Peace Prize<\/a> in 1968 for his work in drafting the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Universal_Declaration_of_Human_Rights\" title=\"Universal Declaration of Human Rights\">Universal Declaration of Human Rights<\/a>, adopted by the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/United_Nations\" title=\"United Nations\">United Nations<\/a> <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/United_Nations_General_Assembly\" title=\"United Nations General Assembly\">General Assembly<\/a> on 10 December 1948. That same year, he was also awarded one of the UN's own <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/United_Nations_Prize_in_the_Field_of_Human_Rights\" title=\"United Nations Prize in the Field of Human Rights\">Human Rights Prizes<\/a>. Ren\u00e9 Cassin founded the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/French_Institute_of_Administrative_Sciences_(IFSA)\" title=\"French Institute of Administrative Sciences (IFSA)\" class=\"mw-redirect\">French Institute of Administrative Sciences (IFSA)<\/a> which was recognized as a public utility association.<\/p>","name":"Ren\u00e9 Cassin","place_of_birth":null,"place_of_death":null,"text":"Ren\u00e9 Cassin , Peace, 1968","year":1968.0}